==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loment
<hw>Lo"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lomentum</ets> a mixture of bean meal and rice, used as a cosmetic
wash, bean meal, fr. <ets>lavare</ets>, <ets>lotum</ets>, to
wash.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An elongated pod, consisting, like
the legume, of two valves, but divided transversely into small cells,
each containing a single seed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lomentaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
